# Frontend Design

Create distinctive, production-grade frontend interfaces that avoid generic "AI slop" aesthetics.

## When to Apply

- Building new UI components, pages, or applications
- User asks for "beautiful", "stunning", "creative", or "distinctive" interfaces
- Creating landing pages, dashboards, or marketing sites
- User complains about generic or boring design

## Design Thinking

Before coding, commit to a **BOLD** aesthetic direction:

| Direction | Characteristics |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Brutally Minimal | Lots of whitespace, stark contrasts |
| Maximalist Chaos | Dense information, overlapping elements |
| Retro-Futuristic | Neon accents, geometric shapes |
| Luxury/Refined | Subtle gradients, serif fonts |
| Editorial/Magazine | Strong typography, grid-based |
| Brutalist/Raw | Exposed structure, monospace fonts |

## Typography: Fonts to AVOID

```css
/* ❌ NEVER - Generic AI slop */
font-family: Inter, Roboto, Arial, system-ui, sans-serif;
```

## Distinctive Font Pairings

| Display Font | Body Font | Use Case |
|--------------|-----------|----------|
| Clash Display | Satoshi | Agency portfolios |
| Playfair Display | Source Sans Pro | Magazines |
| Space Grotesk | DM Sans | SaaS dashboards |
| Cormorant Garamond | Lato | High-end e-commerce |

## Color: Commit to Dominant + Accent

```css
/* ✅ GOOD: Dominant with sharp accent */
:root {
  --bg-primary: #0a0a0b;      /* 70% */
  --bg-secondary: #1a1a1d;    /* 20% */
  --accent: #ff3366;          /* 10% */
}
```

## Motion: High-Impact Moments

```css
/* Orchestrated page load with staggered reveals */
.hero-title { animation-delay: 0.1s; }
.hero-subtitle { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
.hero-cta { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
```

## Anti-Patterns

| Avoid | Why |
|-------|-----|
| Purple gradient on white | Overused, generic |
| Inter/Roboto fonts | Seen everywhere |
| 12-column grid everywhere | Predictable |
| Card soup layout | No visual hierarchy |

